ommute/Defs.html#Commute\">Commute</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> → <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Commute/Defs.html#Commute\">Commute</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/CStarAlgebra/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Unital.html#cfc\">cfc</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For `a` selfadjoint, an element commutes with `cfc f a` if it commutes with `a`.\n\nIf the base ring is `ℝ` or `ℝ≥0`, see `Commute.cfc_real` or `Commute.cfc_nnreal` which don't require\nthe `IsSelfAdjoint` hypothesis on `a` (due to the junk value `cfc f a = 0`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/CStarAlgebra/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Commute.html#IsSelfAdjoint.commute_cfc","kind":"theorem","line":82,"name":"IsSelfAdjoint.commute_cfc","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/CStarAlgebra/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Commute.lean#L82-L89"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/CStarAlgebra/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus/Commute.html#Commute.cfc\"><span class=\"name\">Commute</span>.<span class=\"name\">cfc</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"imp